What does the find / -name part of this really mean, how does the grammer of it work, i ask so i can use it myself on other stuff
Working principle: this is a system that finds the docker compose file in a file structure with a lookup command that will usually give a long list of errors. It then uses 2>/dev/null to basically send all the errors
to the bin. 
2>/dev/null Dev/null is effectively a predetermined unfillable folder that just deletes anything put in it, i guess. 
2> is a reference to output redirection. 
0> means its an input (stdin - standard input)
1> means its a normal output (stdout)
2> means its an error output (stderr)
> : the ">" means to redirect something somewhere, so if it sees those before it it knows what kind of data its redirecting, so its redirecting all error messages to the bin. 

